"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-medal-winning-blitzboks-due-back-in-south-africa-heres-when-date-breaking-news\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbMedal-winning Blitzboks due back in South Africa: Here's WHEN  The Blitzboks won Team SA's first medal at the Paris Olympics 2024 in the rugby sevens. They are due back home this week. Here's when \\u2026  TheBlitzbokswonTeam South Africa'sfirst medalat theParis Olympics 2024in the men's rugby sevens last week.  Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!  The team picked up thebronze medalafter beating Australia26-19in the third-fourth playoff match.  It was thesecondtime in three Olympics that South Africa had won the bronze medal having also done so at the Rio de Janeiro Olympics in 2016.  Every member to the Blitzboks team picked upR50 000as per the financial incentives announced pre-Games by theSouth African Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee (Sascoc).  The coaches involved will also receiveR50 000.  However, as reported byThe South African website, new Minister of Sport, Arts and Culture,Gayton McKenzie, promised that he has a 'big surprise' for all Team SA medal winners, suggesting there could be more prize money coming their way.  Relays and team sportsGold medal: R100 000 per player and the coach R100 000Silver medal: R75 000 per player and the coach R75 000Bronze medal: R50 000 per player and the coach R50 000  Christoffel Grobbelaar, Ryan Oosthuizen, Impi Visser, Zain Davids, Quewin Nortje, Tiaan Pretorius, Shaun Williams, Selvyn Davids, Tristan Leyds, Rosko Specman, Siviwe Soyizwapi, Shilton van Wyk  Reserves:Katlego Letebele, Ronald Brown  Management:Philip Snyman, Ghafoer Luckan, Marius Schoeman, Ashley Evert  The South African men's sevens team will arrive at Cape Town International Airport onTuesday, 30 July.  The team will arrive on Emirates flight EK 770, due to land at16:50.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"